justification: Rhinorrhea, diarrhea, angioedema, and wheezing are common symptoms of anaphylaxis, a severe allergic reaction.}, {diagnosis: Food allergy
justification: Food allergies can cause a range of symptoms, including rhinorrhea, diarrhea, angioedema, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: Drug allergy
justification: Similar to food allergies, drug allergies can manifest with symptoms like rhinorrhea, diarrhea, angioedema, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: Insect sting allergy
justification: Insect stings can trigger allergic reactions, leading to symptoms such as rhinorrhea, diarrhea, angioedema, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: Mastocytosis
justification: Mastocytosis, a disorder characterized by an excess of mast cells, can cause symptoms like rhinorrhea, diarrhea, angioedema, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: Hereditary angioedema
justification: This genetic condition can cause recurrent episodes of swelling (angioedema) along with rhinorrhea, diarrhea, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: ACE inhibitor-induced angioedema
justification: ACE inhibitors, a class of blood pressure medications, can cause angioedema as a side effect, sometimes accompanied by rhinorrhea, diarrhea, and wheezing.}, {diagnosis: Viral infection

justification: Some viral infections can cause a combination of respiratory and gastrointestinal symptoms, including rhinorrhea, diarrhea, wheezing, and sometimes even angioedema.}, {diagnosis: Bacterial infection

justification: Certain bacterial infections, though less common, can also lead to a combination of symptoms like rhinorrhea, diarrhea, wheezing, and potentially angioedema.}, {diagnosis: Idiopathic anaphylaxis
justification: In some cases, anaphylaxis occurs without a clear identifiable trigger, and these cases are classified as idiopathic anaphylaxis.}

justification: Demyelination in the central nervous system can cause a wide variety of neurological symptoms, including ataxia, tinnitus, weakness, and parasthesias.}, {diagnosis: Vitamin B12 deficiency
justification: Vitamin B12 is essential for nerve function, and deficiency can lead to ataxia, weakness, parasthesias, and other neurological symptoms, including tinnitus.}, {diagnosis: Brain tumor
justification: Depending on its location and size, a brain tumor can cause a variety of neurological symptoms, including ataxia, tinnitus, weakness, and parasthesias.}, {diagnosis: Stroke
justification: A stroke affecting the brainstem or cerebellum can cause ataxia, tinnitus, weakness, and parasthesias.}, {diagnosis: Cervical spondylosis
justification: Compression of the spinal cord or nerves in the neck can cause ataxia, weakness, parasthesias, and in some cases, tinnitus.}, {diagnosis: Peripheral neuropathy
justification: Damage to the peripheral nerves can cause ataxia, weakness, and parasthesias, and tinnitus can be a symptom of some types of neuropathy.}, {diagnosis: Migraine with aura

justification: While typically associated with headache, migraine auras can cause a variety of neurological symptoms, including ataxia, tinnitus, weakness, and parasthesias.}, {diagnosis: Lyme disease
justification: Untreated Lyme disease can affect the nervous system, causing ataxia, tinnitus, weakness, and parasthesias.}, {diagnosis: Acoustic neuroma

justification: A tumor on the vestibulocochlear nerve (the nerve that connects the ear to the brain) can cause tinnitus, hearing loss, and problems with balance and coordination (ataxia).}, {diagnosis: Ménières disease

justification: This inner ear disorder can cause vertigo, tinnitus, hearing loss, and a feeling of fullness in the ear. While not a typical symptom, some people with Ménières disease may experience weakness or parasthesias.}
